This paper focuses on improving the performance of generative dialogue models using external knowledge sources, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves incorporating knowledge bases and improving prediction accuracy, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of external knowledge sources also involves information retrieval, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves training neural networks, which is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
